        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "If you try to add an error to a Zend_Form_Element_MultiCheckBox element an php warning will occur:\n{quote}Warning: Invalid argument supplied for foreach() in ........\\library\\Zend\\Form\\Element.php on line 2101{quote}\n\n----\n\nYou can reproduce the error by executing this little snippet:\n{noformat}\n$element = new Zend_Form_Element_MultiCheckBox('someVar');\n$element->addMultiOptions(array('hello', 'world'))\n        ->setLabel(\"Hello world\")\n        ->setRequired(false)\n        ->addError('someError'); \n{noformat} "
