        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/27781",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ice-breaker",
                        "name": "ice-breaker",
                        "displayName": "Tobias Petry",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "There has been a bug in addError some time ago, which affected Zend_Element::addError ([#ZF-3852|http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/browse\/ZF-3852]).\nDon't know if this is a help for anybody.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ice-breaker",
                        "name": "ice-breaker",
                        "displayName": "Tobias Petry",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-01-06T05:04:53.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-01-06T05:04:53.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/27782",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ice-breaker",
                        "name": "ice-breaker",
                        "displayName": "Tobias Petry",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "The codeblock of the library is the following:\n{noformat}\nif ($this->isArray() || is_array($value)) {\n    $aggregateMessages = array();\n    foreach ($value as $val) {\n        $aggregateMessages[] = str_replace('%value%', $val, $message);\n    }\n    $messages[$key] = $aggregateMessages;\n}{noformat}\n\nThe problem seems to be the if-clause. isArray is true, but $value is an empty string, when i run my snippet from above. So the source tries to iterate a string, which does not work and the php-warning for the for-each-loop is thrown.\nI changed the if-clause to make an AND instead of an OR and it does work:\n{noformat}\nif ($this->isArray() && is_array($value)) {\n    $aggregateMessages = array();\n    foreach ($value as $val) {\n        $aggregateMessages[] = str_replace('%value%', $val, $message);\n    }\n    $messages[$key] = $aggregateMessages;\n}{noformat}\n\nSo now, has $value to be an array if we want to loop.\nIt does work, but i don't know if i break something different, but i can't image it, because value HAS TO BE an array for iterating.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ice-breaker",
                        "name": "ice-breaker",
                        "displayName": "Tobias Petry",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-01-06T05:21:20.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-01-06T05:21:20.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/28391",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=joust",
                        "name": "joust",
                        "displayName": "Artur Bodera",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This also breaks when using {{addErrorMessages()}}\nSo there is no good way to display errors with this field.\n\nSee also: ZF-5603 ",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=joust",
                        "name": "joust",
                        "displayName": "Artur Bodera",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-01-22T03:01:15.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-01-22T03:01:15.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/28396",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=joust",
                        "name": "joust",
                        "displayName": "Artur Bodera",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "When using {{addErrorMessages()}} the bug is in {{Zend_Form_Element::_getErrorMessages()}}.\n\nWhen we add error with {{Zend_Form_Element::addError()}} the following is executed:\n{code}\n\/**\n* Add an error message and mark element as failed validation\n*\n* @param  string $message\n* @return Zend_Form_Element\n*\/\npublic function addError($message)\n{\n   $this->addErrorMessage($message);\n   $this->markAsError();\n   return $this;\n}\n{code}\n\nLet's take a look at {{markAsError()}} function:\n\n{code}\n\t$messages       = $this->getMessages();\n\t$customMessages = $this->_getErrorMessages();\n\t$messages       = $messages + $customMessages;\n\tif (empty($messages)) {\n\t\t$this->_isError = true;\n\t} else {\n\t\t$this->_messages = $messages;\n\t}\n\treturn $this;\n{code}\n\nThe problem is in {{_getErrorMessages}} function. The resulting {{$message}} var, in case of {{Multi}} field will look like this:\n{code}\n$messages = array(\n\t0 => array(\n\t\t0 => 'My custom errormessage',\n\t\t1 => 'My custom errormessage',\n\t\t2 => 'My custom errormessage'\n\t)\n)\n{code}\n\nIt's structure is unknown for {{Zend_View_Helper_FormErrors}}, therefore there are errors.\n\nI strongly suggest to give full control over the method of validating {{Multi}} elements! As for now validators are run on each and every selected\nvalue, but there is no way to validate THE WHOLE FIELD, nor give it a GLOBAL SINGLE custom error message. Current architecture does NOT allow i.e. to\ncreate a {{Zend_Validate_Count}} which would throw error if less (or more) number of fields have been selected.\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=joust",
                        "name": "joust",
                        "displayName": "Artur Bodera",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-01-22T03:44:50.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-01-22T03:44:50.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/30676",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ice-breaker",
                        "name": "ice-breaker",
                        "displayName": "Tobias Petry",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This patch resolves the problem.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ice-breaker",
                        "name": "ice-breaker",
                        "displayName": "Tobias Petry",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-05-05T04:09:24.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-05-05T04:09:24.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/34411",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ice-breaker",
                        "name": "ice-breaker",
                        "displayName": "Tobias Petry",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "added new patch with unit tests.\n\ncurrent Zend_Form trunk is defect, test with 1.9.2 final, it's working with no side effects.",
